    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-09-08T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-09-08T03:00:00-05:00" n="76"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d76">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>/9–848:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iraq</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wadsworth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Baghdad</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-09-08T11:00:00+03:00"
                            >September 8, 1948—11 a. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>520. <gloss target="#t_reDeptel1">ReDeptel</gloss> 319, September 5 [<hi
                        rend="italic">3</hi>]. Reference successor to Syria on <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>, Jamali informs me as follows:</p>
                <p>As result Prime Minister’s recent political discussion other Arab capitals, Iraq
                    Govt position has been “modified”.</p>
                <p>All Arab states want an Arab state to succeed Syria. Their preference will be
                    decided at ILPC [<hi rend="italic">ALPC</hi>] meeting Alexandria this week.
                    Egypt is favored. Iran’s concurrence stands (as reported <gloss
                        target="#t_mytel1">mytel</gloss> 499 August 22), Pakistan concurrence has
                    now been received.</p>
                <p>Only indication India’s attitude was given by Mrs. Pandit in conversation with
                    Syrian Minister to Moscow when she asked Arab support for India candidacy.
                    Syrian Govt answer was that Arab states would be happy support India if India
                    would support an Arab state.</p>
                <p>Arab states have also gained impression Turkey will support an Arab state if only
                    in recognition strong Arab support given Turkey candidacy for <gloss
                        target="#t_ECOSOC1">ECOSOC</gloss> last fall.</p>
                <p>Copies by pouch to Athens, Ankara, Cairo, Damascus.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wadsworth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
